User stories, in descending order of priority with estimated difficulty:

	(5)As a player, I want to access the game via a web browser so that I 
	can play on a variety of platforms and specific devices.

	(15)As a player, I want to be able to place my ships

	(10)As a player, I want to be able to select my target square

	(30)As a player, I want to be able to play against other players

	(10)As a player, I want to be able to see mine and my opponent's hits
	and misses on my board(s)

	(1)As a player, I want to be notified when either player has lost
	all of their ships, so I can know the outcome of the game and end it

	(5)As a player, I want to be notified when a single ship belonging to
	either player is sunk

	(15)As a player, I want to land on a main menu from which I can access
	features, start a game and to which I may return when a game ends.

	(10)As a player, I want players to have a limited amount of time to
	take a turn, to prevent games being deadlocked by AFK players, 
	linkdead players, etc.

	(5)As a player, I want to be able to forfeit a game at any time.

	(5)As a player, I want to be able to start a game with a specific 
	player, specified by their current username in the game.

	(10)As a player, I want to be able to start a game with a random other
	player, chosen by the game

	(10)As a player, I want to be able to view my current win/loss totals

	(10)As a player, I want to be able to view the win/loss scores of
	other users, and compare my totals to theirs.

	(20)As a player, I want to be able to communicate somehow with my
	opponent.
